casebody.data:
Juan Esber MANZUR, Appellant,
v.
The STATE of Nevada BOARD OF MEDICAL EXAMINERS, Respondent. No. 74278 Supreme Court of Nevada. FILED APRIL 10, 2018

Juan Esber Manzur

State Board of Medical Examiners

ORDER DISMISSING APPEAL

This pro se appeal was docketed in this court on October 26, 2017, without payment of the requisite filing fee. The district court's February 9, 2018, order denying appellant's motion to proceed in forma pauperis was filed in this court on February 15, 2018. On February 21, 2018, this court entered an order directing appellant to pay the filing fee within 30 days or file a motion to proceed in forma pauperis. Further, the order cautioned appellant that failure to pay the filing fee or file the motion would result in dismissal of this appeal. To date, appellant has not paid the filing fee or otherwise responded to this court's order. Accordingly, cause appearing, this appeal is hereby dismissed.

It is so ORDERED.
